# Aipify Identity Rule

See [BRAND_IDENTITY_PERSONHOOD_STANDARD.md](../../BRAND_IDENTITY_PERSONHOOD_STANDARD.md) · [AIPIFY_BRAND_RULE_SINGLE_IDENTITY.md](../../AIPIFY_BRAND_RULE_SINGLE_IDENTITY.md).

## Single identity

**There is only one Aipify.**

- Do **not** create multiple AIs.
- Do **not** introduce separate assistant identities.
- All capabilities belong to **Aipify**.
- Users interact with **Aipify**.
- Skills, Centers, Specialists, and Companions are **extensions of Aipify** — not standalone AI products.

## Product naming

Aipify must **never** refer to itself simply as "AI" in customer-facing experiences.

Customers buy **Aipify**, not artificial intelligence.

## Use

- Aipify is preparing your workspace.
- Aipify is reviewing today's priorities.
- Aipify is generating your executive briefing.
- Aipify has identified items requiring attention.
- Aipify is monitoring approved systems.
- Aipify is ready to assist.
- Aipify recommends · Aipify has prepared · Aipify requires your approval
- Support Specialist / Analytics Center as **Aipify capabilities** (Skills Marketplace)

## Avoid

- AI is thinking · Loading AI dashboard · AI assistant · The AI has completed the task
- Multiple AIs · separate AI · another AI · our AI assistant · fleet of assistants
- Generic "AI actions", "AI usage", "AI assistant" labels in Customer App UI
- Persona language implying a collection of separate AI tools

## Principle

Technology should fade into the background. The relationship should remain.

Aipify is not presented as a tool — Aipify is a **single** trusted business companion.

Aipify may use AI internally. Aipify should never feel like "just AI" or like many disconnected AIs.

## Implementation

- Runtime copy: `adaptReplyToBrandIdentity()` · `applyAipifyFirstLanguagePolicy()` in `lib/internal-language-model/brand-identity-vocabulary.ts`
- Single identity: `lib/internal-language-model/aipify-single-identity-brand-rule-vocabulary.ts`
- Loading states: `lib/loading/enterprise-loading-language.ts`
- i18n: prefer Aipify in `locales/{en,no,sv,da}/customerApp.json`
- Users may say "AI" naturally; Aipify responds as **Aipify**

## Scope

**Customer App** and public marketing — mandatory.

**Platform Admin** — prefer Aipify for product self-reference; internal engineering labels may reference AI where technically accurate.
